        <briefdescription>
<para>Get the available contexts for a given connection. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This server function returns the available contexts value for a given <computeroutput>conn</computeroutput> connection object. The value returned is the one set with <ref refid="group__bt__pacs_1ga12f283d2daf72302a01cefb4a4a8fc70" kindref="member">bt_pacs_conn_set_available_contexts_for_conn</ref> function or the default value set with <ref refid="group__bt__pacs_1ga29a1ec26c1e5e82e02eac39e1088332c" kindref="member">bt_pacs_set_available_contexts</ref> function.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>conn</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Connection object. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>dir</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Direction of the endpoints to get contexts for.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Bitmask of available contexts. </para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="retval"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>BT_AUDIO_CONTEXT_TYPE_NONE</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>if <computeroutput>conn</computeroutput> or <computeroutput>dir</computeroutput> are invalid </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
